The negative Cash Balance was the accounting balance as on 31st March 2020(Opening cash balance). This had arisen
due to the residual transactions for Financial Year 2019-2020 accounted for during 1st April, 2020 to 10th April, 2020
by the RBI. Asper the M/o Finance, D/o Economic Affairs letter dated 31.03.2017, RBIhadmaintained the cash balance
limit of ₹ 5000.37Crores as on 31.03.2020. However, due to reporting of net payment of ₹ 7594.51 Crore as March
transactions by the agency banks, the Cash balance as on 31st March, 2020 was negative.
